divs: Sighting DetailsI recently captured this picture by my new camera. I was able to zoom in all the way to the left of the sun, because I saw an object in the clouds. I viewed this in negative color as well and it showed up as if it was a hot object. I didn't know what I caught till I uploaded my digital pictures the next day. I picked up the hobby of doing astro-photography and related, to examine pictures just to see if I would ever see something, because I have seen strange things before. I'm not sure what this object is, but maybe somebody could look at it. I have more pictures from that day, but couldnt see anything else, and havent checked all of them. I cropped one picture so you can see what I'm seeing, but the other one you can zoom all the way in and see too. Not sure what it could be..
Summary: Rectangle and/or square object near the sun.
